title: 'It is what it is', 'GOAT', and 'quiet quitting' should be banished
Ask HN: Aggregation of salary ranges for CA job?
text:
Is anyone collating salary ranges for jobs posted in California in 2023? Here are a few interesting ones that I found:

* Netflix gives total comp ranges. For one Director position is listed as 330K-1.8M (!) * Google VP positions all listed at $550K (base) * Meta has their pay scales but for two VP positions they have: “ $error/year to $error/year + bonus + equity + benefits We apologize for the inconvenience, please be patient as we work to correct the issue.”

Ask HN: What to do when Google is about to kill your business?
text:
We are having an issue with Google. All of our email is going to spam (including email between team members).

We have a Domain reputation of 100% as per Google's own tool (Postmaster), and we are following all of Google's best practices -> SPF is set correctly, DKIM, DMARC, the emails are only sent when the customer selects to receive an email, and we include a visible unsubscribe link.

Our whole business is paralyzed, and Google customer support doesn't seem able to identify the issue. It has been 2 weeks.

Is there something else we should be doing?

Ask HN: Have you ever written a white paper?
text:
And if so, how did it go?

How long did it take? Did many people read it? Did it help your career?

I'm considering this is a solo consultant, to establish myself as an authority in a small niche. But I can also see it being very time consuming and maybe not effective.
